verses.text_plain: Come, and let us return unto the Lord: for he hath torn, and he will heal us; he hath smitten, and he will bind us up.
verses.verse_html: 1Come, and let us return unto the Lord: for he hath torn, and he will heal us; he hath smitten, and he will bind us up.

tokens.text: and he will bind us up

verses.text_plain: After two days will he revive us: in the third day he will raise us up, and we shall live in his sight.
verses.verse_html: 2After two days will he revive us: in the third day he will raise us up, and we shall live in his sight.

verses.text_plain: Then shall we know, if we follow on to know the Lord: his going forth is prepared as the morning; and he shall come unto us as the rain, as the latter and former rain unto the earth.
verses.verse_html: 3Then shall we know, if we follow on to know the Lord: his going forth is prepared as the morning; and he shall come unto us as the rain, as the latter and former rain unto the earth.

verses.text_plain: O Ephraim, what shall I do unto thee? O Judah, what shall I do unto thee? for your goodness is as a morning cloud, and as the early dew it goeth away.
verses.verse_html:
4O Ephraim, what shall I do unto thee? O Judah, what shall I do unto thee? for your goodness is as a morning cloud, and as the early dew it goeth away. ▼
▼ goodness: or, mercy, or, kindness

footnotes.body_html: ▼ goodness: or, mercy, or, kindness

verses.text_plain: Therefore have I hewed them by the prophets; I have slain them by the words of my mouth: and thy judgments are as the light that goeth forth.
verses.verse_html:
5Therefore have I hewed them by the prophets; I have slain them by the words of my mouth: and thy judgments are as the light that goeth forth. ▼
▼ and…: or, that thy judgments might be, etc

footnotes.body_text: ▼ and…: or, that thy judgments might be, etc
footnotes.body_html: ▼ and…: or, that thy judgments might be, etc

verses.text_plain: For I desired mercy, and not sacrifice; and the knowledge of God more than burnt offerings.
verses.verse_html: 6For I desired mercy, and not sacrifice; and the knowledge of God more than burnt offerings.

verses.text_plain: But they like men have transgressed the covenant: there have they dealt treacherously against me.
verses.verse_html:
7But they like men have transgressed the covenant: there have they dealt treacherously against me. ▼
▼ men: or, Adam

verses.text_plain: Gilead is a city of them that work iniquity, and is polluted with blood.
verses.verse_html:
8Gilead is a city of them that work iniquity, and is polluted with blood. ▼
▼ polluted: or, cunning for

footnotes.body_html: ▼ polluted: or, cunning for

verses.text_plain: And as troops of robbers wait for a man, so the company of priests murder in the way by consent: for they commit lewdness.
verses.verse_html:
9And as troops of robbers wait for a man, so the company of priests murder in the way by consent: for they commit lewdness. ▼
▼ by…: Heb. with one shoulder, or, to Shechem
 , ▼
▼ lewdness: or, enormity

footnotes.body_text: ▼ by…: Heb. with one shoulder, or, to Shechem
footnotes.body_html: ▼ by…: Heb. with one shoulder, or, to Shechem

verses.text_plain: I have seen an horrible thing in the house of Israel: there is the whoredom of Ephraim, Israel is defiled.
verses.verse_html: 10I have seen an horrible thing in the house of Israel: there is the whoredom of Ephraim, Israel is defiled.

verses.text_plain: Also, O Judah, he hath set an harvest for thee, when I returned the captivity of my people.
verses.verse_html: 11Also, O Judah, he hath set an harvest for thee, when I returned the captivity of my people.
